newsitem.title: UK: Euro VGO strong on supplies, good U.S. buying.
newsitem.headline: Euro VGO strong on supplies, good U.S. buying.

text.p: European vacuum gas oil was firm on lack of supplies and strong U.S. buying interest with the open arbitrage opportunity.
Traders said high and low sulphur barge material was almost non-existent.
"You can't find it on barges and any cargoes are being snapped up by the Americans," said one European trader.

Low sulphur cargoes were also scarce and prices steady. A small parcel was sold on Friday at $155 fob. Although it was not clear where the cargo was headed, dealers said there was also renewed interest in NWE.

High sulphur was also fairly tight and at least one trader was looking to move a cargo transatlantic. Demand from the U.S. was expected to last for the next couple of weeks if the arbitrage stays open, traders said. -- London Newsroom, +44 171 542 8980
